            ">Who is a woman?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/uk-supreme-court-ruling-woman-defined-by-biological-sex.png" alt="UK Supreme Court rules legal definition of ‘woman’ is based on biological sex" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>UK Supreme Court rules that the official definition of a ‘woman’ is based on biological traits. Credits: CediRates
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">In recent debates on gender and biological identity, the UK Supreme Court handed down its <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-17-04-2025-h1-1-judgement?source=wbsite" target="_blank">judgment</a>. In a unanimous ruling, the court clarified that the term “woman” in the Equality Act 2010 refers to biological classification, not gender acquired through a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-17-04-2025-h1-2-gender-recognition-certificate?source=wbsite" target="_blank">Gender Recognition Certificate</a>.<p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
        The decision came after <i>For Women Scotland</i> challenged the Scottish government, which had included trans women in legislation aimed at improving gender balance on public boards. The court stated that including trans women under the official definition would make the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-17-04-2025-h1-3-equality-act?source=wbsite" target="_blank">Equality Act</a> “incoherent,” undermining protections based on biological traits.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
